content.description: sit start with left hand on outside edge, right hand on crummy side pull. feet on the small crimpy ledge. slide your left hand up and right hand to a higher slight side pull crimp and right foot up to a small crimp around my knee and then foot up to knee height crimp. Both hands go to the top, both feet move up to another crimp ledge then super high right foot crimp rail and top out.
content.location: the boulder is directly to the left of the parking spot.

content.description: Left hand continues to slide up the left side of the boulder, right hand starts on a side pull crimp and feet start on a crimp rail. Slide your left hand up, put your right foot on a knee height crimp rail, stand and bump your right hand to another crimp side pull (looks like a triangle kind of). Bump left foot up to another knee height crimp rail then bump right foot to crimp rail right above your left foot. Right hand to the top, match right and left feet then match hands on top. High right foot onto a crimp rail then top out.
content.location: directly to the right of the parking spot, good safe place for crashpads, only need one.

content.description: Sit start on the low arete to the right of Cooper's Booty, move left across the slight overhang on crimps above the lip, and finish on Cooper's Booty.
content.location: Sit start on the corner of the D.B. Cooper boulder that is closest to the parking lot.

content.description: Start on the boulder on climbers right of the Dorsal Fin boulder.  Execute a fun reach move and top it out.
A nice warm up style boulder problem on the obvious north face of the boulder near the small parking spot.
Stand start with hands on a low flake and move to a crimp on the edge of the overhang. Reach up to a sloper, cut the feet, get the right leg up on top of the overhang, and top out.
content.location: Looking from the road, maybe 20 paces the left of the Dorsal Fin boulder.

content.description: These boulders are located next to the pullout and have some good easy climbs.
